<h2>Solar Incentives in Raleigh</h2>
<p>Raleigh residents can take advantage of several attractive solar incentives to reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, before stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. North Carolina offers additional state-level incentives, including property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase your property taxes. Duke Energy provides net metering, allowing customers to receive retail rate credits for excess solar power fed back into the grid. The utility also offers rebates through their solar rebate program, though availability can be limited and operates on a first-come, first-served basis. Additionally, North Carolina's Renewable Energy Tax Credit has historically provided state-level tax incentives, though residents should verify current program availability as state incentives can change.</p>

