<p>When selecting a solar installer in Raleigh, prioritize companies with proper North Carolina electrical contractor licensing and NABCEP (North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners) certified installers. Look for companies with extensive local experience in Wake County, as they'll understand local permitting requirements, Duke Energy interconnection procedures, and climate-specific installation best practices for the hot-humid environment. Verify that installers offer comprehensive warranties, including 25-year panel warranties, 10-year inverter warranties, and workmanship guarantees of at least 5-10 years. Request multiple quotes from established local installers, check Better Business Bureau ratings, and read recent customer reviews focusing on installation quality, timeline adherence, and post-installation support. Reputable Raleigh solar companies should provide detailed energy production estimates, handle all permitting and Duke Energy paperwork, and offer monitoring systems to track your system's performance over time.</p>

